The Kaduna State government has announced four new cases of COVID-19 in three communities in the State. The communities are Kaduna South, Kaduna North and Chikun. It also confirmed that one COVID-19 patient is due for discharge. “Covid-19 Update: One patient is due for discharge. Six positive results were recorded from 60 samples that were tested,” the government tweeted on its verified Twitter page on Sunday night. “Four of the new cases are from Kaduna South and one each from Kaduna North and Chikun,” he added. DAILY POST had reported that the Kaduna State Government had earlier confirmed COVID-19 cases in the Southern Kaduna. Meanwhile, the number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria as of today is 12,486, according to the NCDC.